Wells Fargo Awards $3.5 Million in Restricted Stock Bonuses

-- B y   D a k i n   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-02-24T20:23:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/wells-fargo-awards-3-5-million-in-restricted-stock-bonuses.html
  Wells Fargo & Co ., the largest U.S.
home lender, gave top managers restricted share rights valued at
$3.5 million, including more than $766,000 for Chief Executive
Officer  John Stumpf .  Wells Fargo announced bonuses for at least 11 executives,
awarding 111,250 shares based on the price at the close of
trading on Feb. 22, according to filings today by the San
Francisco-based bank. Timothy J. Sloan, named chief financial
officer Feb. 8 when Howard I. Atkins stepped down, received more
than $716,000 in restricted stock rights.  Chief Administrative Officer Patricia Callahan, the top
executive in charge of managing the Wachovia Corp. integration,
received $500,000 in restricted share rights. Wholesale banking
chief David Hoyt and general counsel James Strother each
received share rights valued at $333,000, according to filings.  The disclosures represent only a portion of the
compensation awarded by Wells Fargo to its senior executives.
More details will be available in the companyâ€™s proxy,
spokeswoman  Mary Eshet  said in an interview.  The awards vest on March 15 in three installments starting
in 2012 and going through 2014. Each executive must hold at
least 50 percent of the acquired shares, measured after-tax, for
at least one year after retirement, according to the filings.  David Carroll, head of the wealth, brokerage and retirement
unit, Chief Risk Officer Michael Loughlin and Mark Oman, head of
the consumer finance and mortgage business, received 5,312
restricted share rights, giving each a stake valued at almost
$167,000.  Avid Modjtabai, head of technology and operations, received
awards valued at almost $146,000 while Controller Richard Levy
received almost $117,000. Carrie Tolstedt, community banking
chief, received more than $78,000.  To contact the reporter on this story:
